Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges
(no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer.
Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then
spread out and roast on the top shelf of your #oven{} until golden,
~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Put the @coleslaw mix{120%g} into a #medium bowl{} and mix in half the
@mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix and set aside.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on a medium-high heat. Once hot
add the @British beef mince{240%g}, breaking it up with a #wooden spoon{},
and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Pour in the
@tomato ketchup{1%tbsp} and stir to coat the beef.

> IMPORTANT: The beef is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @water{50%ml}, stir together and and simmer until the moisture has
evaporated and the ketchup and mince are nicely combined. Taste and add @salt{}
and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

> Tip: Start any washing up whilst the wedges cook.

Remove from the heat.

When the wedges are cooked, warm the @plain taco tortillas{6} in the #oven{}
for ~{2%minutes}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g} and reheat the beef
if necessary.

Spread the remaining mayo on the tacos, share these between your plates. Then
top with the beef mince and sprinkle the cheese over your tacos. Serve the
wedges and the slaw on the side. Enjoy!